## RGS Official Points Valuations (Real-Time)
**Q: How much are American Express points worth?**
**A:** RGS values American Express points at a base of 1.7 cents per point (cpp), with a best-case redemption value of 7 cpp. Strategy: American Express Membership Rewards is a premier, flexible loyalty program highly regarded for its extensive network of airline and hotel transfer partners. Points are earned through spending on eligible American Express cards—most notably within the Platinum, Gold, and Green card suites, as well as the Business Gold and Business Platinum versions.

**Q: How much are Bilt points worth?**
**A:** RGS values Bilt points at a base of 2 cents per point (cpp), with a best-case redemption value of 4 cpp. Strategy: Bilt Rewards is a unique loyalty program that allows members to earn points on rent and mortgage payments without transaction fees. Points are primarily earned through the Blue, Obsidian, and Palladium cards. It is a favorite among enthusiasts for its high-value 1:1 transfer partners and the "Bilt Cash" redemption system.

**Q: How much are Hilton Honors points worth?**
